name: Purpose USD Cash Management Fund
longDescription: investing primarily in high-quality debt securities denominated in U.S. dollars, generally maturing in not more than one year. To achieve its investment objectives, the fund intends to have a significant proportion of its portfolio invested in U.S. dollar denominated high-quality short term corporate debt instruments. The fund may also invest in U.S. dollar denominated treasury bills or other short term debt obligations of, or guaranteed by, the Canadian governments or their agencies, Canadian chartered banks, Canadian loan or trust companies or Canadian corporations, as well as U.S. dollar denominated bank-sponsored asset-backed commercial paper which may allow the fund to enhance its yield while maintaining credit quality. Investments made by the fund will be in the top two ratings categories of any of the designated rating organizations (as defined in NI 81-102).
fulldescription: investing primarily in high-quality debt securities denominated in U.S. dollars, generally maturing in not more than one year. To achieve its investment objectives, the fund intends to have a significant proportion of its portfolio invested in U.S. dollar denominated high-quality short term corporate debt instruments. The fund may also invest in U.S. dollar denominated treasury bills or other short term debt obligations of, or guaranteed by, the Canadian governments or their agencies, Canadian chartered banks, Canadian loan or trust companies or Canadian corporations, as well as U.S. dollar denominated bank-sponsored asset-backed commercial paper which may allow the fund to enhance its yield while maintaining credit quality. Investments made by the fund will be in the top two ratings categories of any of the designated rating organizations (as defined in NI 81-102). The fund seeks to earn a high rate of U.S. dollar income, while at the same time preserving capital and maintaining liquidity.
